HEADWORD: Gravestone
<hw>Grave"stone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stone laid over,
or erected near, a grave, usually with an inscription, to preserve the
memory of the dead; a tombstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graveyard</ent>⟦br⟧
